    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 inline-six engine. This unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double VANOS to deliver linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M-differential lock. The chassis has been properly sorted: the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates to prevent floor cracking, and the rod bearings have been replaced as preventative maintenance. The suspension features upgraded bushings and Bilstein dampers, maintaining the signature handling characteristics of the chassis. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with a well-loved driver's car, the drivetrain remains tight and the engine pull is strong across the entire rev range.",
